=Walmart&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYjQUpuL-d6PdnOWp7rsHs40IPlJSo50R_2Nm30fevjV&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FGoogle-Nest-Hub-2nd-Gen-Smart-Home-Display-with-Google-Assistant-Chalk%2F169438279">Google Nest Hub</a> , but those usually have lower-quality screens and aren&#39;t as simple to mount on a wall. <em>— 杰夫·邓恩 (Jeff Dunn)，高级商务作家</em></p><h2>Book of the Month </h2><p><core-commerce id="820947fe7b444fa5a06168e9a8282965" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If you know a teacher who&#39;s still a champion of the printed word, they might appreciate a <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.bookofthemonth.com/gift">Book of the Month subscription</a> . I like how BOTM does the hard work of figuring out what&#39;s new and good in fiction so all I have to do is read. The club selects seven or so books each month for members to pick from, and the selection is diverse enough that most readers will find something to meet their tastes. And if nothing looks good, they can always pick something from the back catalog or skip the month altogether. At first I thought it would be too much pressure to contend with a new book every month, but the option to skip effectively just extends their subscription, so there&#39;s no pressure. You can gift a three, six or twelve month membership for $60, $100 or $200, respectively. <em>- 作为</em></p><h2>Belkin BoostCharge Pro with MagSafe </h2><p><core-commerce id="5da5d09941464105bab766c5f599f683" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> A pick from our guide to the <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-wireless-charger-140036359.html">best wireless chargers</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAaSazTDNL-7adffrUGwxMYttTjavkoek8EnmhxAEEN2_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09WD15ZQ3%2F%3Fth%3D1">Belkin&#39;s BoostCharge Pro</a> is a compact charging pad that should be a useful addition for any iPhone-owning teacher&#39;s desk. It&#39;s MagSafe-compatible, so it can snap magnetically onto the back of any recent iPhone, and it delivers up to 15W of power, which is the fastest rate available for this class of device. It won&#39;t be as quick as using a cable, but there&#39;s a certain pleasure to simply plopping your phone down on it to recharge, and it can still deliver about a 70 percent charge to an iPhone 14 in an hour. The BoostCharge Pro also has a built-in kickstand for propping up a phone to watch videos and the like. This is far from the cheapest charging puck around, but as a gift, it&#39;s a convenient way to top up. Just try to get it with <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAalMhwTSWP18xyM_AfLSCl5O8lEXwrCeOI3o56dyGdFy&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09WD15ZQ3%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1%3Fsmid%3DATVPDKIKX0DER%26th%3D1">a power supply</a> , if possible. <em>— 京东</em></p><h2>Blue light blocking glasses </h2><p><core-commerce id="a23c409875f548309599e3c172921bfe" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Your favorite teacher or professor probably looks at a screen for just as long as you do every day. Blue light blocking glasses can be a great gift since they&#39;ll make it easier for them to get work done while (hopefully) reducing eye strain, headaches and other ailments. These are probably best bought for educators who don&#39;t wear prescription glasses already, since you don&#39;t want to impede their actual eyesight with non-prescription lenses. Plenty of eyewear companies make stylish blue light glasses, but you don&#39;t have to spend an arm and a leg on a pair. <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:PRIVÉ REVAUX;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=8a89061b-0d95-4133-b466-2b506e51c0f8&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=PRIV%C3%89+REVAUX&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI4YTg5MDYxYi0wZDk1LTQxMzMtYjQ2Ni0yYjUwNmU1MWMwZjgiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wcml2ZXJldmF1eC5jb20vY29sbGVjdGlvbnMvYmx1ZS1saWdodC1ibG9ja2luZy1sZW5zZXMiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjY0NzljZjc3LWExZTYtNDdjMi05NzU4LWJmNWRjZTAxZmZiMyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAU6Y9yMDZ6GyWZxa6p87WFoA93W9SzCS5P_tBspG8g0H&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fpriverevaux.com%2Fcollections%2Fblue-light-blocking-lenses">Privé Revaux</a> has a ton of options priced as low as $30 each, or if you have a feeling your teacher would like to swap styles more often, <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASu-X0OH2zzUnaEIlsZILZXYPe2jHLirmUHzAlHDVfxc&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fs%3Fk%3Dblue%2Blight%2Bblocking%2Bglasses%26crid%3D8SNDXPO784AS%26sprefix%3Dblue%2Blight%2Bblocking%2Bglasses%252Caps%252C125%26ref%3Dnb_sb_noss_1">Amazon</a> has a number of multi-packs to choose from. <em>— Valentina Palladino，高级商业编辑</em></p><h2>Headspace </h2><p><core-commerce id="ae1e06e2d89e4688a38f0d0db3172d5d" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The most tenured college professor and the newest preschool teacher could likely use a little more calm in their day, and <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Headspace;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=e3494264-16cf-476b-92a8-2dfe2c12bfa0&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Headspace&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJlMzQ5NDI2NC0xNmNmLTQ3NmItOTJhOC0yZGZlMmMxMmJmYTAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaGVhZHNwYWNlLmNvbS9idXkvZ2lmdCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNjQ3OWNmNzctYTFlNi00N2MyLTk3NTgtYmY1ZGNlMDFmZmIzIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAbuapxRgqme2m8YYiSeJe85Y6g-riRaNxb2Fc5-uofmf&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.headspace.com%2Fbuy%2Fgift">Headspace</a> is one gift idea that can help them get it. The brightly colored self-care app has a slew of meditations, guided breathing sessions and inspirational talks to choose from and each one lists its duration. I often just have a minute or two before I have to get back to what I was doing, and following even a one-minute-long breathing exercise can noticeably change my mood (and posture and general awareness). Headspace includes sleep programs too, like wind-down sessions, stories, white noise sounds and soundscapes. You can gift one year of the service for $70, or three months for $39. <em>- 作为</em></p><h2>Kobo Clara 2e </h2><p><core-commerce id="214eef524fda4b5b89f6e728ea0bedf4" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> We don&#39;t want to make generalizations, but if there&#39;s a segment of the population who likes to read, it&#39;s probably teachers. The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3VzLmtvYm9ib29rcy5jb20vcHJvZHVjdHMva29iby1jbGFyYS0yZSIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNjQ3OWNmNzctYTFlNi00N2MyLTk3NTgtYmY1ZGNlMDFmZmIzIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAcORdAh7RU-yQ_laHfvAXkIB0wD6iiF_2rg2HJ200GLK&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fus.kobobooks.com%2Fproducts%2Fkobo-clara-2e" class="rapid-with-clickid">Kobo Clara 2E</a> is our current <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-ereader-130013808.html">favorite e-reader</a> because it&#39;s easy on the eyes, comfortable to hold and offers the right amount of customization. The waterproof design makes it a good candidate for vacations and pool-side reading, and the warm lights make it easy to read late into the night. Considering Kobo now has an unlimited read and listen subscription in <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Kobo;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=10b363e1-6abb-4fc0-b019-cb4ff191d49a&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Kobo&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIxMGIzNjNlMS02YWJiLTRmYzAtYjAxOS1jYjRmZjE5MWQ0OWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cua29iby5jb20vdXMvZW4vcGx1cyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNjQ3OWNmNzctYTFlNi00N2MyLTk3NTgtYmY1ZGNlMDFmZmIzIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAWZ03N8nJnX6LTxQ8WrmL1rHqO6hxveNGMcahusc7geS&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kobo.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Fplus">Kobo Plus</a> , the company&#39;s well-built devices are even better equipped to compete in a space where Kindles have dominated for years. <em>- 作为</em></p><h2>Bellroy Desk Caddy </h2><p><core-commerce id="813ada49f4d2432d976556decd6f8352" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> They say an organized desk is an organized mind. Whether that&#39;s true or not, it can certainly be difficult to keep track of all the tech you need on a regular basis. <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Bellroy;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3a8ee27e-ede5-433b-be86-c7b2742ab647&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Bellroy&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdT0kbOoHc-kQJonQN0f_gZHMNT7AK0hDMV5l8dM8vBd&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fbellroy.com%2Fproducts%2Fdesk-caddy%3Fcolor%3Dblack%26material%3Dripstop_recycled">Bellroy&#39;s Desk Caddy</a> has pockets, pouches and loops to keep cords, plugs, earbuds, and dongles in their place. The structured shape stands up when you load it, but is flexible enough to fit into a crowded backpack if you need to take it with you. We also like that it&#39;s water resistant and made from recycled materials. <em>- 作为</em></p><h2>Trade Coffee subscription </h2><p><core-commerce id="47fba9f2aa2d4d76b41446ae5fa6b977" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> A <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Trade Coffee;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=dfa88110-059d-4934-8b98-ae689660c6f6&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Trade+Coffee&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJkZmE4ODExMC0wNTlkLTQ5MzQtOGI5OC1hZTY4OTY2MGM2ZjYiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZHJpbmt0cmFkZS5jb20vZ2lmdC1zdWJzY3JpcHRpb24vcC8xODU4IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI2NDc5Y2Y3Ny1hMWU2LTQ3YzItOTc1OC1iZjVkY2UwMWZmYjMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAUxuU4MvJqRwS3_lsePhIk-fLqBgocHSa8Mdh6_WkAgs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.drinktrade.com%2Fgift-subscription%2Fp%2F1858">Trade Coffee subscription</a> can help the teacher in your life shake up their morning cup of joe. It offers a curated selection of more than 450 coffees from across the US and smartly personalizes which ones it recommends to each subscriber. Upon redeeming their gift, your teacher will be prompted to take a brief quiz that asks about their flavor and brew preferences, information Trade will use to suggest a specific bag catered to their taste. They can then give a thumbs-up or thumbs-down to any coffee they receive, which the company considers to hone future recommendations. Managing all of this online is straightforward. You can gift anywhere from two to 24 bags, and Trade says any gift subscriptions will not automatically renew, so nobody will have any surprise charges to deal with down the line. <em>— 京东</em></p><h2>Purist Mover </h2><p><core-commerce id="817012615b484492a9ab734cb287ac2b" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://www.puristcollective.com/products/mover-18oz">Purist Mover</a> is the closest thing to a “premium” water bottle that I&#39;ve tried, with a clean, minimalist stainless steel aesthetic and a satisfying textured finish. Its biggest hook, though, is the ultra-thin layer of glass that lines its interior. Apart from insulating your drink all day, this is designed to keep fluids from gaining a metallic taste or unwanted odors as quickly as they might with other bottles. The whole thing will still need washing every so often, but in my experience, this has actually worked.</p><p> The Mover is an 18oz bottle, but there are <a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.puristcollective.com/collections/all">different size and lid options</a> to choose from (the “Union” spout top is my preference, though it can be somewhat noisy, if that matters). No Purist bottle is especially cheap, but it should make hydrating a little more convenient for your teacher&#39;s day-to-day, on top of providing a nicer piece of design for their desk. <em>— 京东</em></p><h2>Tribit StormBox Micro 2 </h2><p><core-commerce id="9ee90514f24645a38e20a9cc8a5451ba" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> For audio-related lessons in class or just enjoying music while out and about, the <a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcwB2Z0Akzo8kdyUfFfAJulwyxV0rgOCMm65Gy75HTV8&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FTribit-StormBox-Portable-Speaker-Built%2Fdp%2FB09Q59321N">Tribit StormBox Micro 2</a> is a highly portable Bluetooth speaker that pumps out good volume for its compact size. Its playback controls are simple to operate, and its built-in strap lets it connect to things like a bag or bike handlebars on the go. It can also double as a power bank and charge a smartphone in a pinch. A speaker this small will never be the fullest sounding, but for what it is, the Stormbox Micro 2&#39;s audio quality is fine as well. If you like the idea of gifting a portable speaker but want something that sounds richer, though, you can check out our <a data-i13n="cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-portable-bluetooth-speakers-133004551.html">Bluetooth speaker buying guide</a> for more recommendations. <em>— 京东</em></p><h2>Criterion Channel subscription </h2><p><core-commerce id="090f494cb0c74ad9ae38b441ce307611" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If your teacher considers themselves a film buff, a <a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://www.criterionchannel.com/checkout/subscribe/purchase">Criterion Channel subscription</a> might suit their tastes. This is the streaming service of <a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://www.criterion.com/">The Criterion Collection</a> , a video distribution company that restores and preserves a carefully curated selection of acclaimed films that span genres and languages. It doesn&#39;t have the same deluge of content as a Netflix or Prime Video, but it also has a lot less trash.</p><p> The service bundles many films into helpful <a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1" href="https://www.criterionchannel.com/recent-collections">collections</a> , from <a data-i13n="cpos:28;pos:1" href="https://www.criterionchannel.com/afrofuturism">Afrofuturism</a> to<a data-i13n="cpos:29;pos:1" href="https://www.criterionchannel.com/foreign-language-oscar-winners">Foreign-Language Oscar Winners</a> to <a data-i13n="cpos:30;pos:1" href="https://www.criterionchannel.com/short-films-by-david-lynch">Short Films by David Lynch</a> . Various titles come with bonus features like cast interviews as well. Unfortunately, not every film in the Collection is available on the Channel at any given time. (There are <a data-i13n="cpos:31;pos:1" href="https://www.criterion.com/shop/collection/328-gift-cards">gift cards</a> that can go toward films that are only available in physical form.) Nevertheless, for movie-loving teachers who feel like they&#39;ve watched everything on the usual suspects, the service should still provide hours of stimulating works. Gift subscriptions are available in one- to 12-month increments. <em>— 京东</em></p><h2>The Sill plant gifts </h2><p><core-commerce id="42c43ab705c3433da7ce48c30a335571" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> You can&#39;t go wrong with a gift of greenery to show your appreciation for a beloved teacher. You could pick up a flower arrangement locally or send them a fancy one from <a data-i13n="cpos:32;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:The Bouqs Company;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=5f376a87-6193-41c7-8934-eb983c6c1de8&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=The+Bouqs+Company&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI1ZjM3NmE4Ny02MTkzLTQxYzctODkzNC1lYjk4M2M2YzFkZTgiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9ib3Vxcy5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI2NDc5Y2Y3Ny1hMWU2LTQ3YzItOTc1OC1iZjVkY2UwMWZmYjMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZITjv_G-h-rwCoKGhR6-UCZgWVQoX8oLJjnZk2ziuhF&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fbouqs.com%2F">Bouqs</a> or another online service, but something more unique like <a data-i13n="cpos:33;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ae8d92ef-212d-46b6-b6d2-9c317ad5e040&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=The+Sill&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJhZThkOTJlZi0yMTJkLTQ2YjYtYjZkMi05YzMxN2FkNWUwNDAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlc2lsbC5jb20vcGFnZXMvdW5pcXVlLXBsYW50LWdpZnRzIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI2NDc5Y2Y3Ny1hMWU2LTQ3YzItOTc1OC1iZjVkY2UwMWZmYjMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZUwMJNEHMSs_Tz6cZd-_aITjQrq4Y4oS9LxdKKLBsOE&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesill.com%2Fpages%2Funique-plant-gifts"